                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Additio 1 and 2 basically contain the same genealogy. Both are crudely written and partly illegible, from the comparison of both texts the genealogy was constructed.  
The genealogy starts with well known political figures in the history of Tǝgray, ʾƎngǝda ʾƎgziʾ (s. "Ǝndärta" in EAE vol 2, 297) and Yäʿǝbikä ʾƎgziʾ (s. EAE vol. 5, in print), and ends with šum ʿagame Gäbrä Krǝstos, the owner of this Ms.
                        </item>
